properties.Act_Desc: Destroying tires and self-confidence, a tenth of a mile at a time.
Perfect conditions on the trail -- dry rocks, tacky dirt, good flow!
Few different laps in Purgatory on the Truck.
Garmin decided to corrupt a bunch of files and 'forget' the first half of the ride.. such a nice way of reminding me to clear out the memory!
It sounded like a good idea in my head; my legs disagreed. (Shut up legs.)
Found the top of Summit Road along the way.
Busy day on the Velo-way.  And a PR! (It ain't the bike... it's the motor, or something like that...)
East Campus (detail); Central Campus (primary disconnections); West Campus (early explorations).
Buddy from Iowa asked how Winter was going -- thought I'd grab a few clips and show him: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PHEYA1oLCvU
Blue jeans and denim ride; didn't sweat a drop! (Ok, so 'feels' was 36F)
Long commute to Freeman Center field site.
Round Two -- getting in most of the trails, missed Blind Salamander and the Crushed Climb though.
Thanks to elpaalo and a tailwind...
Das Hugel reminded me how much I enjoyed the long-distance hustles -- knocked out a quick (sub-4hr) 100km before hitting the "control point" (Shipleys!)
Foggy with temps in the 40's to start -- but after the first 40 miles, the sun came out and kept the course over 60 until the sun dipped a bit low.
456 mile loop: Fulton Ranch, Summer Mountain Ranches, Hugo-Purgatory, Wagner & Neighborhood, Hoffman Lane, Hunter Road.  (Added a few extra miles in town to make my 100km goal for the day).
Sitting here wondering why it was such a painful ride --- then seeing a list of PR's...  thanks for the good pace Friends (I'll pull longer, slower next time, I promise)!
